      <h3>üèùÔ∏è What are Islands?</h3>
      <p>Islands are interactive components that load JavaScript only when needed. This page is mostly static HTML with islands for interactivity.</p>
      <p><strong>This page loads minimal JavaScript</strong> - only the interactive components below will have JavaScript loaded.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Interactive Demos</h2>
    <p style="text-align: center; color: #6b7280; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      These components demonstrate different loading strategies for islands.
    </p>

    <div class="demo-grid">
      <div class="demo-card">
        <h3>Counter (Load)</h3>
        <p>This counter loads immediately when the page loads.</p>
        <island src="./islands/Counter.plk" client:load>
          <div class="loading-placeholder">
            Loading counter...
          </div>
        </island>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-card">
        <h3>Timer (Idle)</h3>
        <p>This timer loads when the browser is idle.</p>
        <island src="./islands/Timer.plk" client:idle>
          <div class="loading-placeholder">
            Loading timer...
          </div>
        </island>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-card">
        <h3>Chart (Visible)</h3>
        <p>This chart loads when it becomes visible in the viewport.</p>
        <island src="./islands/Chart.plk" client:visible>
          <div class="loading-placeholder">
            Loading chart...
          </div>
        </island>
      </div>
    </div>

    <pre class="code-block"><code>&lt;!-- Counter loads immediately --&gt;
